        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/20/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 07:39:12</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=3300"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3300')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=71604&TOPIC_ID=8837&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Favorite+right+clicky+item&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I will add to my post...just cause I'm bored and a dork.</P><P>Still CoS is the top for me.  Since I have inate running speed 3 now, my Jboots are retired.  Kilamon, on Tunare you can pick up pre-nerf ones for 4-6kpp.</P><P>I find the stalking probes very useful R-click items.  Mush less expensive than the hog beads.  For those unfamiliar, a tinkerer can make stalking probes which are small/tiny items that do not stack but cast Eye of Zomm with 5 charges.  You can buy them for 25-30pp each.  When you expend all the charges, they resell for 11-15pp to a vendor.  VERY NICE to have around.  If you group with a non-pet class, then you can have them cast the eye for you to eat when you have a pet up.  Not something I use everyday and I cannot justify the cost of hog beads.  But nice to have in your bag of tricks.  Every necro 49 and up should have something that casts eye of zomm.  It saves a ton of downtime when you get your ass handed to you and barely get away. </P><P>For those not quite sure how to use them, you put them in an empty inv slot, switch to a 3rd person view.  Click the probe.  Click on the summoned eye to target it.  Cast vex or BoD.  Sit.  Enjoy the hp.  You perspective will shift to the eye when you cast it...so it is easier to target it in 3rd person view.  After you eat your eyeball and it dies, then your perspective shifts back to your body.  </P><P>And another tip for peeps.  If you bank is not filled with 10 slot items you can go to the gnomes in Iceclad and buy the Deluxe Toolboxes for less than 2 pp each.  These are weight 3.5 stone 10-slot boxes.  Very nice and cheap.</P><P>I use my rotting trousers now instead of memming the 55th level augmentation.  Easier to outdamage the pet when it is augmented with the trousers and you don't have that annoying gazzilion minute wait to cast the spell after memming it.  If I had my EoT spell, I guess I could use the 55th level spell and still not worry about my pet outdamaging me. </P><P>I do use the rotting wristband as well.  But the manna recoup is negligible for me.  Just easier to click an item than type /pet get lost</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
