        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">1) Shrouds of Earthen Shadow...<BR>Plain and simple it rocks.  Helps me pull when I want to (less aggro is good).  Makes travel easy.  And it's just simply the best in convienance for me right now.  The only downside is I never Skin of the Shadow anymore.</P><P>2)Rotting Pantaloons...  I just like the text "Your Rotting Pantaloons begin to glow." or is it Trousers?  Bleh I haven't used it in so long I've forgotten :(.</P><P>3)Scythe of the Shadowed Soul, nothing quite like having an epic named after your guild.  Free snare is good.  Mana-free kite with my Chicken-Stick is also nice.  It also means I use next to no mana in a group (bone ring would be a nice addition to the mana-free setup).</P><P>4) Robe of the Bonecaster, the effort saved on this robe is alot.  And since the difference between it and Rotting is a whole 1Ac, -2MR, +5DR/CR, +5Cha, +1Int, it's not really a big trade off.</P><P>The Blight be upon ye.<BR>Crimson Claw<BR>Shadowed Soul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
